# specmap.snapshot ‚Äî the "before" graph (¬ß4.3)

Captured from a live `cargo xtask specmap` regen at branch `cultural-refactor`
head `be7a92c` (host `8831a14`). The regenerated `specmap.json` was **reverted**
(`git checkout -- specmap.json`) ‚Äî the committed index stays at its parked,
drifted baseline (CONTINUE: "specmap regen ‚Äî regen when M1 lands"). The baseline
that ¬ß4.9 gate 1 protects is the **fact set below**, not a committed file. A live
regen reads the current tree, so before/after dangling comparisons are valid
regardless of the committed json's staleness.

## The graph (live regen)
- **711** spec units ¬∑ **589** tagged code items ¬∑ **603** edges.

## The dangling set ‚Äî what gate 1 protects
- **‚àÖ ‚Äî 0 suspects, 0 warnings.** The tree is internally consistent: every code
  `#[spec]`/`#[verifies]`/`scope!` edge resolves (host `spec://vibevm/‚Ä¶` + the one
  `[[external_specs]]` ‚Üí `core-ai-native`). **Gate 1 = this stays 0.**

## Known orphan ‚Äî recorded so it does NOT count as "new"
- `vibe_resolver::embedded_provider::EmbeddedPrecedence` (enum) at
  `crates/vibe-resolver/src/embedded_provider.rs:18` ‚Äî untagged `pub enum` from the
